From 0000000000000000000000000000000000000000 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Samuel Attard <sattard@anthropic.com>
Date: Wed, 13 May 2026 11:54:44 -0700
Subject: feat: carry embedder startup data in CreateNewWindowReply
MIME-Version: 1.0
Content-Type: text/plain; charset=UTF-8
Content-Transfer-Encoding: 8bit

When a renderer calls window.open() with no URL, the new window's
RenderFrame, its synchronous about:blank document, and its embedder
preload scripts are all created inside the renderer's window.open()
call stack — between the CreateNewWindow sync IPC returning and the
call returning to page script. There is no other browser-to-renderer
transport that can reach the new frame before its DidCreateScriptContext
fires, so the embedder cannot deliver per-window startup data (preload
scripts, environment, code caches) that the embedder may have customized
for the new window during CreateNewWindow.

Add an opaque BigBuffer field to CreateNewWindowReply, populated via a
new ContentBrowserClient::GetExtraCreateNewWindowReplyData() hook (called
unconditionally; the embedder decides whether to return data — Electron
returns it only for windows that stay on about:blank, since a window
that navigates gets the data through the normal navigation flow), and
consumed via a new ContentRendererClient::SetPendingCreateNewWindowStartupData()
hook called before the new RenderFrame is created so it can be picked up
by RenderFrameCreated() on the same call stack.

diff --git a/content/browser/renderer_host/render_frame_host_impl.cc b/content/browser/renderer_host/render_frame_host_impl.cc
index 7a391a954494cf558406574de8a3b4318242bf3c..45622e1dd5249aeb29bb066271c56c64aa464801 100644
--- a/content/browser/renderer_host/render_frame_host_impl.cc
+++ b/content/browser/renderer_host/render_frame_host_impl.cc
@@ -10538,7 +10538,12 @@ void RenderFrameHostImpl::CreateNewWindow(
       new_main_rfh->GetSiteInstance()->browsing_instance_token(),
       delegate_->GetColorProviderColorMaps(),
       /*widget_screen_rect=*/std::nullopt,
-      /*window_screen_rect=*/std::nullopt);
+      /*window_screen_rect=*/std::nullopt,
+      /*electron_startup_data=*/std::nullopt);
+
+  reply->electron_startup_data =
+      GetContentClient()->browser()->GetExtraCreateNewWindowReplyData(
+          new_main_rfh, params->target_url);
 
   new_main_rfh->render_view_host()->RenderViewCreated(new_main_rfh);
 
